    "markdown": "Musubi is a personal website framework that uses Notion as a CMS, powered by Nuxt.\nPosts, pages, and site settings like the title, nav links and timezone are all in Notion. There's no admin panel and no config file to edit.\nEach build reads Notion and outputs static HTML, so the published site doesn't call Notion at all.",
